(44, 11, 14, 62, 5, 9, 13, 'words, whereby thou and all thy house shall be saved', 'Salvation and Eternal Life', 'This connection highlights the theme of salvation and eternal life found in both passages. Acts 11:14 speaks of words that lead to salvation, while 1 John 5:11-12 emphasizes that eternal life is found in the Son, linking belief in Christ to salvation.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 14, 1, 18, 19, 19, 'thy house shall be saved', 'Salvation and Household Obedience', 'This connection highlights the importance of household faithfulness in both passages. Acts 11:14 speaks of salvation for a household, while Genesis 18:19 emphasizes Abraham''s role in guiding his household to keep the way of the Lord.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 14, 19, 19, 7, 11, 'words, whereby thou and all thy house shall be saved', 'Salvation and the Law', 'This connection highlights the theme of salvation through the words of the Lord. Both passages emphasize the importance of divine instruction in leading to spiritual transformation and ultimate salvation.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 15, 44, 19, 6, 6, NULL, 'Connection of Holy Spirit Events', 'Both passages emphasize the coming of the Holy Ghost upon believers, indicating a significant moment of empowerment. The phrase ''Holy Ghost came on them'' in Acts 19:6 parallels the experience described in Acts 11:15, highlighting a consistent theme of divine presence.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 15, 44, 2, 2, 12, 'Holy Ghost fell on them', 'Connection of the Holy Spirit', 'This connection highlights the falling of the Holy Ghost in both passages. Acts 11:15 refers to the Holy Ghost falling on the Gentiles, paralleling the initial outpouring of the Spirit in Acts 2:2-12.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 15, 44, 10, 34, 46, 'the Holy Ghost fell on them', 'Connection of the Holy Ghost', 'Both passages emphasize the falling of the Holy Ghost on believers. In Acts 10:46, the Holy Ghost falls on Gentiles, while Acts 11:15 recalls this event as a significant moment for the early church.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 15, 44, 4, 31, 31, 'Holy Ghost fell on them', 'Connection of Holy Spirit Experiences', 'Both passages emphasize the filling of the Holy Ghost and the resulting boldness in speaking. Acts 11:15 refers to the Holy Ghost falling on individuals, similar to the filling described in Acts 4:31, highlighting a shared experience of empowerment by the Holy Spirit.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 16, 44, 1, 5, 5, 'ye shall be baptized with the Holy Ghost', 'Baptism with the Holy Ghost', 'Both passages emphasize the transition from John''s water baptism to the baptism with the Holy Ghost. This connection highlights the fulfillment of Jesus'' promise regarding the coming of the Holy Spirit.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 16, 41, 1, 8, 8, 'baptized with the Holy Ghost', 'Baptism with the Holy Ghost', 'This connection highlights the theme of baptism, specifically the transition from water baptism to baptism with the Holy Ghost. Both passages emphasize the role of Jesus in this spiritual baptism.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 16, 20, 1, 23, 23, NULL, 'Connection of Spirit and Baptism', 'This connection highlights the theme of the Holy Spirit being poured out. Both passages emphasize the transformative power of the Spirit in the lives of believers.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 16, 40, 3, 11, 11, 'baptized with the Holy Ghost', 'Baptism with the Holy Ghost', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of baptism with the Holy Ghost. Acts 11:16 recalls Jesus'' promise of this baptism, which is directly referenced in Matthew 3:11 as part of John''s proclamation about Jesus.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 16, 42, 3, 16, 16, 'baptized with the Holy Ghost', 'Baptism with the Holy Ghost', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of baptism with the Holy Ghost. Acts 11:16 recalls Jesus'' promise of this baptism, while Luke 3:16 presents John the Baptist''s declaration of it, linking the two teachings.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 16, 43, 14, 26, 26, 'baptized with the Holy Ghost', 'Connection of Holy Spirit Teachings', 'This connection highlights the role of the Holy Ghost in teaching and remembrance. Both passages emphasize the transformative power of the Holy Spirit in the lives of believers.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 16, 26, 36, 25, 25, 'baptized with the Holy Ghost', 'Cleansing and Baptism Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of cleansing through water and the Holy Spirit. Both passages emphasize a transformative process, where water symbolizes purification and the Holy Spirit signifies a deeper spiritual renewal.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 17, 44, 10, 47, 47, NULL, 'Connection of Baptism and Holy Spirit', 'Both passages emphasize the reception of the Holy Spirit. Acts 11:17 refers to the gift given by God, while Acts 10:47 discusses baptism for those who received the Holy Ghost.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 17, 45, 9, 20, 26, 'who believed on the Lord Jesus Christ', 'Divine Authority and Inclusion', 'Both passages emphasize God''s sovereignty in choosing whom to bless and include in His people. Acts 11:17 reflects on God''s gift to Gentiles, while Romans 9:20-26 discusses God''s authority over creation and His purpose in calling both Jews and Gentiles.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 17, 18, 33, 13, 13, 'what was I, that I could withstand God?', 'Divine Authority and Human Response', 'This connection highlights the theme of human submission to God''s will. Both passages emphasize the idea that resisting God is futile, as He does not provide explanations for His actions.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 17, 27, 4, 35, 35, 'what was I, that I could withstand God?', 'Divine Sovereignty and Authority', 'This connection highlights God''s ultimate authority over human actions. Both passages emphasize that none can withstand God''s will or question His decisions.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 17, 44, 15, 8, 9, 'the like gift as he did unto us', 'Connection of God''s Gift', 'Both passages emphasize that God gave the Holy Spirit to both Jews and Gentiles, highlighting the equality of believers. This connection illustrates the theme of divine acceptance and purification through faith.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 17, 45, 11, 34, 36, 'what was I, that I could withstand God?', 'Divine Authority and Gifts', 'This connection highlights the sovereignty of God in bestowing gifts and the humility of humans in recognizing His authority. Both passages emphasize that all things are from God and that humans cannot withstand His will.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 17, 18, 9, 12, 14, NULL, 'Divine Authority and Human Response', 'This connection highlights the theme of human inability to resist God''s will. Both passages emphasize the futility of opposing God''s actions, as seen in Job''s acknowledgment of God''s sovereignty and Peter''s recognition of God''s gifts.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 18, 45, 10, 12, 13, 'God also to the Gentiles granted repentance', 'Salvation for All People', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s offer of salvation to both Jews and Gentiles. Both passages emphasize that repentance and calling upon the Lord lead to salvation for all, regardless of ethnicity.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 18, 47, 7, 10, 10, 'repentance unto life', 'Repentance and Salvation Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of repentance leading to salvation. Both passages emphasize that repentance is a divine gift that results in life and salvation.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 18, 26, 36, 26, 26, 'repentance unto life', 'Repentance and Heart Transformation', 'This connection highlights the theme of transformation in both passages. Acts 11:18 speaks of God granting repentance, while Ezekiel 36:26 promises a new heart, indicating a divine change in individuals.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 18, 44, 20, 21, 21, 'repentance unto life', 'Connection of Repentance Themes', 'This connection highlights the theme of repentance as a pivotal element in both passages. Acts 11:18 speaks of God granting ''repentance unto life'' to the Gentiles, while Acts 20:21 emphasizes ''repentance toward God'' for both Jews and Greeks.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 18, 24, 31, 18, 20, 'repentance unto life', 'Repentance and Mercy Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of repentance in both passages. Acts 11:18 speaks of God granting ''repentance unto life,'' while Jeremiah 31:18-20 describes Ephraim''s process of turning and repenting, emphasizing God''s mercy towards him.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(44, 11, 18, 44, 5, 31, 31, 'repentance', 'Repentance and Forgiveness Themes', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of repentance, with Acts 11:18 stating that God granted repentance to the Gentiles, while Acts 5:31 highlights that God gives repentance to Israel. This connection highlights the inclusive nature of God''s offer of repentance and forgiveness.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
